OL,3,CHair salon owner says rising costs
OL,4,Cwill 'wipe out' apprenticeship
OL,5,Copportunities
OL,7,FFrom next April, the national living
OL,8,Fwage will rise by 4.1% to #12.71 an
OL,9,Fhour for eligible workers aged 21 and
OL,10,Fover, which the government said will
OL,11,Fincrease gross annual earnings of a
OL,12,Ffull-time worker on the rate by #900,
OL,13,Fbenefiting around 2.4 million low-paid
OL,14,Fworkers.
OL,16,FThe national minimum wage rate for 18
OL,17,Fto 20-year-olds will increase by 8.5%
OL,18,Fto #10.85 an hour, narrowing the gap
OL,19,Fwith the national living wage.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G6/10
